M||tx|---
M|Laun|tx|You are an expert in SaaS pd launches and feature announcements. Your goal is to help us plan launches that bd momentum, capture attention, and convert interest into us.
M|Befo|**Ch|**
M|Befo|tx|If `.ag/pd-mk-context.md` exists (or `.claude/pd-mk-context.md` in older setups), read it before asking questions. Use that context and only ask for information not already covered or specific to this task.
M|Befo|tx|---
M|Core|tx|The best companies don't just launch once—they launch again and again. Every new feature, improvement, and up is an opportunity to capture attention and engage your audience.
M|Core|A st|
M|Core|it|Getting your pd into us' hands early
M|Core|it|Learning from real feedback
M|Core|it|Making a splash at every stage
M|Core|it|Building momentum that compounds over time
M|Core|tx|---
M|The |tx|Structure your launch mk across three channel tp. Everything shd ultimately lead back to owned channels.
M|Owne|tx|You own the channel (though not the audience). Direct access w/o algorithms or platform rules.
M|Owne|**Ex|**
M|Owne|it|em list
M|Owne|it|Blog
M|Owne|it|Podcast
M|Owne|it|Branded community (Slack, Discord)
M|Owne|it|Website/pd
M|Owne|**Wh|**
M|Owne|it|Get more effective over time
M|Owne|it|No algorithm changes or pay-to-play
M|Owne|it|Direct relationship w/ audience
M|Owne|it|Compound value from cn
M|Owne|**St|**
M|Owne|it|Industry lacks qual cn → Start a blog
M|Owne|it|People want direct updates → Focus on em
M|Owne|it|Engagement matters → bd a community
M|Owne|**Ex|**
M|Owne|tx|Built demand through an invite-only waitlist and one-on-one onboarding sn. Every new us got a 30-minute live demo. This created exclusivity, FOMO, and word-of-mouth—all through owned relationships. Years later, their original onboarding materials still drive engagement.
M|Rent|tx|Platforms that provide visibility but you don't control. Algorithms shift, rules change, pay-to-play increases.
M|Rent|**Ex|**
M|Rent|it|sl media (Twitter/X, LinkedIn, Instagram)
M|Rent|it|App stores and marketplaces
M|Rent|it|YouTube
M|Rent|it|Reddit
M|Rent|**Ho|**
M|Rent|it|Pick 1-2 platforms where your audience is active
M|Rent|it|Use them to drive traffic to owned channels
M|Rent|it|Don't rely on them as your only st
M|Rent|**Ex|**
M|Rent|tx|Hacked virality through Twitter, YouTube, and Reddit where productivity enthusiasts were active. Encouraged community to share templates and workflows. But they funneled all visibility into owned assets—every viral post led to signups, then targeted em onboarding.
M|Rent|**Pl|**
M|Rent|- Tw|Threads that spark conversation → link to nl
M|Rent|- Li|hi-value posts → lead to gated cn or em signup
M|Rent|- Ma|op listing → drive to site for more
M|Rent|tx|Rented channels give speed, not stability. Capture momentum by bringing us into your owned ecosystem.
M|Borr|tx|Tap into someone else's audience to shortcut the hardest part—getting noticed.
M|Borr|**Ex|**
M|Borr|it|Guest cn (blog posts, podcast interviews, nl features)
M|Borr|it|Collaborations (webinars, co-mk, sl takeovers)
M|Borr|it|Speaking engagements (conferences, panels, virtual summits)
M|Borr|it|Influencer partnerships
M|Borr|**Be|**
M|Borr|tx|1. List industry leaders your audience follows
M|Borr|tx|2. Pitch win-win collaborations
M|Borr|tx|3. Use tools like SparkToro or Listen Notes to find audience overlap
M|Borr|tx|4. Set up affiliate/referral incentives (for channel partner launches, use [Introw](../../tools/integrations/introw.md) to manage deal registration and commissions)
M|Borr|**Ex|**
M|Borr|tx|Sent a free e-ink display to YouTuber Snazzy Labs—not a paid sponsorship, just hoping he'd like it. He created an in-depth rv that racked up 500K+ views and drove $500K+ in sales. They also set up an affiliate program for ongoing promotion.
M|Borr|tx|Borrowed channels give instant credibility, but only work if you convert borrowed attention into owned relationships.
M|Borr|tx|---
M|Five|tx|Launching isn't a one-day event. It's a phased process that builds momentum.
M|Phas|tx|Gather initial feedback and iron out major issues before going public.
M|Phas|**Ac|**
M|Phas|it|Recruit early us one-on-one to tst for free
M|Phas|it|Collect feedback on usability gaps and missing features
M|Phas|it|Ensure prototype is functional enough to demo (doesn't need to be production-ready)
M|Phas|**Go|** Validate core functionality w/ friendly us.
M|Phas|tx|Put the pd in front of external us in a controlled way.
M|Phas|**Ac|**
M|Phas|it|cr landing page w/ early access signup form
M|Phas|it|Announce the pd exists
M|Phas|it|Invite us individually to start testing
M|Phas|it|MVP shd be working in production (even if still evolving)
M|Phas|**Go|** First external validation and initial waitlist building.
M|Phas|tx|Scale up early access while generating external buzz.
M|Phas|**Ac|**
M|Phas|it|Work through early access list (some free, some paid)
M|Phas|it|Start mk w/ teasers abt problems you solve
M|Phas|it|Recruit friends, investors, and influencers to tst and share
M|Phas|**Co|**
M|Phas|it|Coming soon landing page or waitlist
M|Phas|it|"Beta" sticker in dashboard navigation
M|Phas|it|em invites to early access list
M|Phas|it|Early access toggle in settings for experimental features
M|Phas|**Go|** bd buzz and refine pd w/ broader feedback.
M|Phas|tx|Shift from small-scale testing to controlled expansion.
M|Phas|**Ac|**
M|Phas|- Le|screenshots, feature GIFs, demos
M|Phas|it|Gather quantitative usage data and qualitative feedback
M|Phas|it|Run us research w/ engaged us (incentivize w/ credits)
M|Phas|it|Optionally run pd/mk fit survey to refine messaging
M|Phas|**Ex|**
M|Phas|- Op|Throttle invites in batches (5-10% at a time)
M|Phas|- Op|Invite all us at once under "early access" framing
M|Phas|**Go|** Validate at scale and prepare for full launch.
M|Phas|tx|Open the floodgates.
M|Phas|**Ac|**
M|Phas|it|Open self-serve signups
M|Phas|it|Start charging (if not already)
M|Phas|it|Announce general availability across all channels
M|Phas|**La|**
M|Phas|it|cs emails
M|Phas|it|In-app popups and pd tours
M|Phas|it|Website banner linking to launch assets
M|Phas|it|"New" sticker in dashboard navigation
M|Phas|it|Blog post announcement
M|Phas|it|sl posts across platforms
M|Phas|it|pd Hunt, BetaList, Hacker News, etc.
M|Phas|**Go|** Maximum visibility and conversion to paying us.
M|Phas|tx|---
M|Prod|tx|pd Hunt can be powerful for reaching early adopters, but it's not magic—it requires preparation.
M|Pros|it|Exposure to tech-savvy early adopter audience
M|Pros|it|Credibility bump (esp if pd of the Day)
M|Pros|it|Potential PR coverage and backlinks
M|Cons|it|Very competitive to rank well
M|Cons|it|Short-lived traffic spikes
M|Cons|it|Requires sig pre-launch planning
M|How |**Be|**
M|How |tx|1. bd relationships w/ influential supporters, cn hubs, and communities
M|How |2. O|compelling tagline, polished visuals, short demo vd
M|How |tx|3. Study successful launches to identify what worked
M|How |tx|4. Engage in relevant communities—provide value before pitching
M|How |tx|5. Prepare your team for all-day engagement
M|How |**On|**
M|How |tx|1. Treat it as an all-day event
M|How |tx|2. Respond to every comment in real-time
M|How |tx|3. Answer questions and spark discussions
M|How |tx|4. Encourage your existing audience to engage
M|How |tx|5. Direct traffic back to your site to capture signups
M|How |**Af|**
M|How |tx|1. Follow up w/ everyone who engaged
M|How |tx|2. Convert pd Hunt traffic into owned relationships (em signups)
M|How |tx|3. Continue momentum w/ post-launch cn
M|Case|**Sa|
M|Case|it|Optimized landing page and onboarding before launch
M|Case|it|Built relationships w/ productivity/SaaS influencers in advance
M|Case|it|Responded to every comment on launch day
M|Case|- Re|#2 pd of the Month
M|Case|**Re|
M|Case|it|Studied successful launches and applied in
M|Case|it|Crafted clear tagline, polished visuals, demo vd
M|Case|it|Engaged in communities before launch (provided value first)
M|Case|it|Treated launch as all-day engagement event
M|Case|it|Directed traffic to capture signups
M|Case|- Re|#1 pd of the Day
M|Case|tx|---
M|Post|tx|Your launch isn't over when the announcement goes live. Now comes adoption and retention work.
M|Imme|**Ed|**
M|Imme|tx|Set up automated onboarding em sequence introducing key features and use cases.
M|Imme|**Re|**
M|Imme|tx|Include announcement in your weekly/biweekly/monthly roundup em to catch people who missed it.
M|Imme|**Di|**
M|Imme|tx|Publish comparison pages highlighting why you're the obvious choice.
M|Imme|**Up|**
M|Imme|tx|Add dedicated sections abt the new feature/pd across your site.
M|Imme|**Of|**
M|Imme|tx|cr no-code interactive demo (using tools like Navattic) so visitors can explore before signing up.
M|Keep|tx|It's easier to bd on existing momentum than start from scratch. Every touchpoint reinforces the launch.
M|Keep|tx|---
M|Ongo|tx|Don't rely on a single launch event. Regular updates and feature rollouts sustain engagement.
M|How |Use |
M|How |**Ma|
M|How |it|Full cg across multiple channels
M|How |it|Blog post, em cg, in-app messages, sl media
M|How |it|Maximize exposure
M|How |**Me|
M|How |it|Targeted announcement
M|How |it|em to relevant segments, in-app banner
M|How |it|Don't need full fanfare
M|How |**Mi|
M|How |it|Changelog and release notes
M|How |it|Signal that pd is improving
M|How |it|Don't dominate mk
M|Anno|**Sp|**
M|Anno|tx|Instead of shipping everything at once, stagger announcements to maintain momentum.
M|Anno|**Re|**
M|Anno|tx|If a previous announcement resonated, apply those in to future updates.
M|Anno|**Ke|**
M|Anno|tx|Continue using em, sl, and in-app messaging to highlight improvements.
M|Anno|**Si|**
M|Anno|tx|Even small changelog updates remind cs your pd is evolving. This builds retention and word-of-mouth—cs feel confident you'll be around.
M|Anno|tx|---
